title: Vanished Arizona: Recollections of the Army Life of a New England Woman
creator: Martha Summerhayes
description: LibriVox recording of VANISHED ARIZONA: RECOLLECTIONS OF THE ARMY LIFE OF A NEW ENGLAND WOMAN, by MARTHA SUMMERHAYES. "This is the lively autobiography of Martha Summerhayes, the wife of an officer in the American Army. Here, she tells many stories about life and conditions in different camps and forts in which she lived with her expanding family, people along the way, and Journeys." (Summary by Stav Nisser) For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org. M4B format available
subject: librivox; audiobook; memoirs; autobiography; americana; arizona; military; western
source: Librivox recording of a public-domain text

reviews.reviewbody: An autobiographical chronicle of hardships, joys and sorrows. Well written and rich with the minutia of daily life, which far from being mundane, loom large when actual survival is at stake. A must if you are interested the history of the American West. Good to excellent readers.(Though only one seemed to know how to pronounce "Gila.")
reviews.reviewtitle: Vivid account of army life on the western frontier
